args: Ugh. Could I BE more pathetic?
I can't even entertain the one person\nI admire most in all the world.
Owwwww... And now my stomach\npains are even worse!
I will be fine. Please just\nleave me alo—Owwwww!
I'm not going to leave you alone\nwhen you're clearly suffering.
Please, just go. Don't make me\nfeel worse than I already do.
I am fully cognizant of the fact I am\nworthless and pathetic, thank you.
The only way I could be more pathetic is\nif you started to pity—Owwwww!
I'm not going to pity you, Julietta;\nbut I also won't leave you like this.
If your stomach hurts so much that\nyou're nearly in tears, there's clearly\nsomething serious going on.
I'm sure Elly is completely disgusted\nwith me.
All I wanted to do was give her\na chance to relax from fighting.
But all I DID was ruin her holiday!
I was trying to give her a good time,\nbut ended up only thinking of myself.
I caused her no end of stress,\nand even put her life in danger!
What kind of holiday is that?\nI've made her more tired than ever!
She must find me utterly exhausting.
Well, no. Not with words, anyway.\nBut I am certain she thinks it.

I know how much you adore Elisanne,
and I understand why you would.
So tell me: does that REALLY sound
like something she would say?
If you're this concerned about it,\nyou should ask her yourself.
Don't put words in her mouth;\nhear them for yourself.
I think she's well aware of how hard\nyou've worked to make her happy.
Even though all my plans failed?
Let Elisanne be the judge of that.\nLook, she's right over there.
Julietta! I have been looking\neverywhere for you!
I tried making ice-brewed tea earlier,\njust as you taught me.
I was hoping you might try some and...
Wait... What's wrong?\nWhy are you crying?
Oh, are you worried about something?\nPerhaps I can be of assistance.
W-well, Elisanne... I was wondering...\nHow was today for you?
Do you feel like you were able to relax?\nLike you were truly on holiday?
Did you...enjoy spending time with me?
Do not lie to make me feel better!\nI know the truth of the matter!
All of my plans were utter disasters.
This is no lie—I truly enjoyed myself.
I could tell how much thought you put\ninto ensuring I had a good time.
And I very much appreciated the chance\nto let my hair down and relax a little.
I swear it by the goddess Ilia;\nyou gave me a wonderful holiday.
A wonderful... *sniff* Oh, what a relief!\n*sniff* *sniiiiiiff*
Oh, but I have been SO worried!\nI thought you had a horrid time!
You have nothing to worry about.
I enjoyed all of our activities—volleyball,\ntea time, AND the walk at the cove.
The only thing I don't like is seeing\nyou cry on my behalf just now.
After all, if I am having fun,\nI want you to have it with me.
*sniff* J-just stop already!\nI want to stop crying!
First tears of sadness, now tears of\nrelief... *sniff*
If you were so worried about whether\nI was having a good time, Julietta,\nwhy didn't you simply ask?
Can you not even trust me with that?
N-no! It's not like that at all!\n*sniff* Oh, I'm so sorry...
I was putting words in your mouth\nand worrying myself sick over them.
I need to trust people more, Elisanne.\nI need to trust YOU more.
Nothing would make me happier.\nAfter all, I trust you a great deal.
(Dancing across the battlefield,\nour lives in each other's hands,\ntrusting each other completely...)
(And there I am, ever at Elly's side!\nYes... Yes, I like it very much!)
I won't give up! I swear it!
I'm not quite certain what that means,\nbut I'm glad to see you feeling better.
Me too. And now that we've settled that,\nperhaps now is a good time to try that\ntea you made, Elisanne.
Oh, yes! I want some, very much!
There's no time to lose.\nLet's hurry back!
Oh, what a fine day this turned out to be!
